data.description:
HUGE lot, HUGE house! This unique two-story home is in a quiet neighborhood offering a serene living experience with AMPLE space. There have only been two owners of this property!
Here are the highlights:
Five bedrooms plus an office/flex room. Two stories. Very spacious, with LOTS of interior storage. Large bedrooms. Stone countertops. Recently remodeled second floor bathroom. LED lighting in every room, and the main rooms have dimmer switches. New range and dishwasher. Built-in microwave. The dining nook and living room are separated from the kitchen. This house has both a heat pump and a natural gas furnace. The back door and side door are brand new. Lot is just under one acre, and the large back yard is perfect for kids or animals, and can also be accessed from the dead end side street; large side street access. AMPLE space for parking along side street. Front yard is huge as well and boasts large, mature silver maple trees. Zoned as R-2 Urban Estate Dwelling, this home offers versatility, allowing for animals, even horses. Furnace was extensively repaired one year ago. The home is on well water and septic. There is a hydrant in the back yard as well. Large, two story shed in back yard. Located near Sooner and Danforth it is just a two-minute drive to the I-35 access and the new Crest grocery store, seven minutes to Integris hospital, and about the same to the Lake Arcadia bike trail parking lot!
